    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-04T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-04T15:00:00-05:00" n="248"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.857 Athenia/33: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-04T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 4, 1939—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 4—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1441. The Admiralty has informed the Embassy regarding the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Athenia</hi> as follows:</p>
                <p>Survivors in one of the rescuing ships state that submarine was clearly seen and
                    have no doubt that ship was torpedoed. From evidence up to date about 1000 have
                    been saved out of a possible 1400, including crew. Every effort is being made to
                    find out if any United States citizens are killed or injured. The Admiralty
                    state that no British mines were laid in the vicinity. Evidence of Chief Officer
                    is that ship was torpedoed without warning. Submarine fired a round at ship on
                    surfacing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
